sect1.para:
Green and Dimino Luong (
               2023
            ), in discussing the concept of territorialism, noted that both formal and informal leaders within organizations that have exhibited bullying behaviors often have historically done so and use their knowledge of the organization to positively and negatively impact others. The fear of loss of perceived power and loss of control drives the employees who embody territorialism to bully others. In order to disrupt the bully who uses territorialism to stand their ground in their familiar department or unit, changing their environment and co-workers can be the start of the end of their reign.
